items.title: Rubio Visits Panama Canal
items.description: On his first foreign trip as secretary of state, Marco Rubio met with President José Raúl Mulino and visited the Panama Canal.

items.title: Crews Lift Wreckage From D.C. Plane Crash Out of Potomac
items.description: A crane was removing the fuselage of the American Airlines jet, which crashed into the river last week after colliding with a U.S. Army helicopter.

items.title: French Court Convicts Director Christophe Ruggia in #MeToo Case
items.description: Christophe Ruggia was sentenced to four years and fined for sexually assaulting the actress Adèle Haenel when she was a minor.

items.title: With Trump’s Backing Uncertain, Europe Scrambles to Shore Up Its Own Defenses
items.description: European leaders will gather Monday to plot a rough path forward on defense. Wavering support from President Trump is likely to drive the debate.
